Arrays :
==================================================
Arrays is data structure used to store collection of information.

	1) Array stores only homogeneous information.
	2) In Java, arrays store homogeneous elements â€” all elements must be of the same data type.
	3) Arrays Declaration need to be done with capacity
	4) Once an array is created, its size is fixed and cannot be changed.
	5) Array is nothing but object , inside object of array array index will present that index start from zero.
====================================================================================================
Types of Array :
===========================================
	i)	Single dimensional Array
	ii)	Two Dimensional Array
	iii)Three Dimensional Array
====================================================================================================
	int[] arr = new int[5];  // Declaration + creation
	arr[0] = 10;
	arr[1] = 20;
====================================================================================================

	int[][] matrix = new int[2][3];  // 2 rows, 3 columns
	matrix[0][0] = 1;
	matrix[0][1] = 2;
====================================================================================================

	int[][][] cube = new int[2][2][2];

====================================================================================================



